episodes.title: For All Debts Public and Private
episodes.plot: Chris puts a ghost from his past to rest, while Carmela grows uneasy about her future.

episodes.title: No Show
episodes.plot: Chris' success earns him some jealousy, Adriana learns the truth about her friend, and Meadow still claims that Jackie Jr.'s death still weighs heavily on her.

episodes.title: Christopher
episodes.plot: Columbus Day ignites tensions between Italians and Native Americans, and Bobby receives devastating news about his wife.

episodes.title: The Weight
episodes.plot: A joke sparks a series of hit contracts, while Carmela finds herself happier than perhaps she should be that Furio will be around for good.

episodes.title: Pie-o-My
episodes.plot: Ralph buys a racehorse, but Tony ends up more attached to it than Ralphie is. Carmela starts trying to invest in her future.

episodes.title: Everybody Hurts
episodes.plot: Tony feels depressed over the negative impact he has on people who don't deserve it, while Carmela tries to set up Furio with a friend, AJ is uncomfortable with his girlfriend's wealth, Artie attempts a new business venture.

episodes.title: Watching Too Much Television
episodes.plot: Adriana learns that life is not like TV shows, while Tony discovers that a former girlfriend has moved on, along with Ralphie and others they scam the Department of Housing and Urban Development.

episodes.title: Mergers and Acquisitions
episodes.plot: Paulie has to take care of some rough relationships for his mother, while Tony's fancy for a fellow horse fancier lands him in trouble with Carmela.

episodes.title: Whoever Did This
episodes.plot: Ralph's callous behavior finally steps over the line, while Chris gets deeper into his heroin addiction and Uncle Junior's mental capacity begins to become in question.

episodes.title: The Strong, Silent Type
episodes.plot: In the midst of suspicions that he killed Ralph, Tony tries to intervene to get Chris clean and sober.

episodes.title: Calling All Cars
episodes.plot: Tony's dreams seem to tell him where his life is headed, but he still feels as though he's out of control.

episodes.title: Eloise
episodes.plot: Carmela and Furio grow too close for safety, while Paulie discovers that he's not as big a fish as he thought he was.

episodes.title: Whitecaps
episodes.plot: Junior's trial comes to an end, but Tony's trials are just getting underway. Also, the Sopranos almost purchase a house on the beach.
